statements: SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE age > 50
SELECT patient_id, age, gender FROM PatientData WHERE gender='Male'
SELECT patient_id, medical_condition FROM PatientData WHERE telemedicine_usage = true
SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE age BETWEEN 20 AND 30 ORDER BY gender ASC
SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE medical_condition LIKE '%diabetes%' ORDER BY age DESC
SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY patient_id DESC;
SELECT gender, COUNT(*) AS total_patients FROM PatientData GROUP BY gender HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 ORDER BY total_patients DESC;
SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE medical_condition LIKE '%diabetes%' AND telemedicine_usage = TRUE;
SELECT AVG(age) AS average_age, MAX(age) AS max_age, MIN(age) AS min_age FROM PatientData;
SELECT patient_id, age, gender, telemedicine_usage FROM PatientData WHERE gender = 'Male' ORDER BY age ASC, patient_id DESC;
SELECT * FROM patients;
SELECT patient_name, age, diagnosis FROM patients WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY patient_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM health_records WHERE heart_rate > 80 ORDER BY date DESC;
SELECT patient_id, gender FROM patients WHERE gender = 'Female';
SELECT record_id, temperature, blood_pressure FROM health_records WHERE temperature > 98.6 ORDER BY record_id ASC;
SELECT patient_name, age, diagnosis FROM patients WHERE age > 30 AND gender = 'Male';
SELECT * FROM health_records WHERE date > '2022-01-01' AND temperature > 98.6;
SELECT patient_name, diagnosis, temperature FROM patients JOIN health_records ON patients.patient_id = health_records.patient_id WHERE diagnosis = 'COVID-19' AND heart_rate > 100;
SELECT patient_name, age, heart_rate FROM patients LEFT JOIN health_records ON patients.patient_id = health_records.patient_id WHERE heart_rate < 60 OR blood_pressure = 'High';
SELECT patient_name, gender, blood_pressure FROM patients JOIN health_records ON patients.patient_id = health_records.patient_id WHERE blood_pressure LIKE '%High%' ORDER BY gender DESC;
SELECT * FROM patient_data ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT patient_id, gender FROM patient_data WHERE gender = 'Female';
SELECT location FROM patient_data WHERE age > 40;
SELECT * FROM telemedicine_records WHERE diagnosis LIKE '%flu%';
SELECT strategy_name, implementation_date FROM public_health_strategies ORDER BY implementation_date ASC;
SELECT * FROM patient_data ORDER BY age DESC, gender ASC
SELECT pd.patient_id, pd.age, tr.diagnosis FROM patient_data pd JOIN telemedicine_records tr ON pd.patient_id = tr.patient_id WHERE tr.diagnosis LIKE '%flu%'
SELECT tr.patient_id, tr.appointment_date, pd.location FROM telemedicine_records tr JOIN patient_data pd ON tr.patient_id = pd.patient_id WHERE pd.age > 50 ORDER BY tr.appointment_date DESC
SELECT * FROM public_health_strategies WHERE implementation_date > '2021-01-01' ORDER BY strategy_name

SELECT pd.patient_id, pd.gender, tr.diagnosis, phs.strategy_name FROM patient_data pd JOIN telemedicine_records tr ON pd.patient_id = tr.patient_id JOIN public_health_strategies phs ON pd.patient_id = phs.strategy_id WHERE pd.gender = 'Female' AND tr.diagnosis LIKE '%cough%' ORDER BY pd.patient_id ASC
SELECT * FROM patients ORDER BY patient_id DESC;
SELECT patient_name, date_of_birth FROM patients WHERE gender='Male';
SELECT diagnosis, doctor_name FROM medical_records WHERE consultation_date >= '2022-01-01';
SELECT patient_id, start_time, end_time FROM telemedicine_sessions WHERE consultation_type='Follow-up';
SELECT * FROM public_health_data WHERE population_density > 1000 ORDER BY disease_prevalence ASC;
SELECT * FROM patients;
SELECT patient_name, date_of_birth, address FROM patients WHERE gender = 'Female';
SELECT COUNT(*) as total_patients FROM patients;
SELECT patient_id, patient_name, diagnosis, consultation_date FROM patients LEFT JOIN medical_records ON patients.patient_id = medical_records.patient_id;
SELECT patient_id, diagnosis, start_time, end_time FROM medical_records JOIN telemedicine_sessions ON medical_records.patient_id = telemedicine_sessions.patient_id;
SELECT * FROM Patient;
SELECT patient_id, name, age, gender FROM Patient WHERE age > 30;
SELECT patient_id, name, city, insurance FROM Patient WHERE city = 'New York';
SELECT diagnosis, treatment, timestamp FROM MedicalRecord ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT study_id, study_name, start_date, end_date, description FROM ResearchStudy WHERE lead_researcher = 'Dr. Smith';
SELECT * FROM Patient WHERE age > 60 ORDER BY name DESC
SELECT name, gender, city FROM Patient WHERE insurance = 'Medicare' AND age BETWEEN 30 AND 50

SELECT Patient.name, MedicalRecord.diagnosis, TelemedicineUsage.duration_minutes FROM Patient INNER JOIN MedicalRecord ON Patient.patient_id = MedicalRecord.patient_id INNER JOIN TelemedicineUsage ON Patient.patient_id = TelemedicineUsage.patient_id WHERE TelemedicineUsage.consultation_type = 'Virtual' ORDER BY Patient.name ASC

SELECT PublicHealthData.city, PublicHealthData.population, AVG(PublicHealthData.health_index) AS average_health_index FROM PublicHealthData GROUP BY PublicHealthData.city HAVING AVG(PublicHealthData.health_index) > 75 ORDER BY average_health_index DESC

SELECT Patient.name AS patient_name, ResearchStudy.study_name, ResearchStudy.start_date, ResearchStudy.lead_researcher FROM Patient JOIN MedicalRecord ON Patient.patient_id = MedicalRecord.patient_id JOIN ResearchStudy ON Patient.city = ResearchStudy.lead_researcher ORDER BY ResearchStudy.start_date ASC
